{
  "stem": "17526.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "They were taken out to the woods and they were told this is going to be their territory and from here they're going to start sabotaging the German support-- we've got to do something, we can't just sit like this here and see our mothers and fathers being taken away to wherever.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "We didn't know of crematoriums at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "We knew we will never see them again.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "It was a-- it was a very rational.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "But there-- it was a trap, unfortunately.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "And I can see his face.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "And I-- every time I talk about it, I get choked up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "I can see his face and we argued so fiercely.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "That was the part-- there was an underground, there were attempts to resist the Germans, but unfortunately, they were wiped out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "Life in the houses and the apartments was-- became unbearable.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "Hunger and deprivation, they dehumanized us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "They degraded us, they-- they made a joke of us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "They grabbed people on the street and they cut off their beards.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "They made us lay down and do all kinds of acts of unspeakable things and we had to live with it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And then after this big selection, there were smaller selections.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "But then they realized that it's too much of a-- an ordeal.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they have given out lists and the Jewish [GERMAN] commander, the council, through the militia, through the Jewish militia-- who were wearing special arm bands and special white hats-- of course, needless to say that we had to wear the Star of David on every garment that we were wearing.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And once you were caught without it, you were severely punished or shot.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For the slightest transgression, you were shot.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
